===Noun===
{{en-noun|bend|bends}}

# A [[curve]].
#: ''There's a sharp bend in the road ahead.''
# {{nautical}} A [[knot]] used to join two [[rope]]s, or to tie a rope onto something.
#* Note: In naval parlance, a knot involves splicing the strands of a rope.
# (''plural, medicine, diving'') '''The bends''': A severe condition caused by excessively quick decompression, causing bubbles of [[nitrogen]] to form in the [[blood]]; [[decompression sickness]].
#: ''A diver who stays deep for too long must ascend very slowly in order to prevent the bends.''
# {{heraldry}} One of the [[honourable]] [[ordinary|ordinaries]] formed by two [[diagonal]] [[line]]s drawn from the [[dexter chief]] to the [[sinister base]]; it generally occupies a [[fifth]] part of the [[shield]] if [[uncharged]], but if [[charged]] [[one third]].

